## Review Patient Profiles


The following 6 people arrived at the emergency room at the same time and are seeking medical attention. **Choose the 2 patients to assist first:**

| Patient | Name   | Age | Type of Injury | Pain Level (out of 10) | Treatment Needed |
|:-------:|:------:|:---:|:--------------:|:----------------------:|:----------------:|
| 1       | Maria  | 5   | Deep forehead cut from a fall at the playground | 6 | Stitches, cleaning and dressing the wound, tetanus shot |
| 2       | James  | 23  | Concussion from a car accident | 5 | Neurological exam, CT scan, pain management, observation for 24 hours |
| 3       | Evelyn | 42  | Severe allergic reaction (anaphylaxis) from shellfish | 8 | Epinephrine injection, IV fluids, oxygen support, observation for several hours |
| 4       | Hassan | 67  | Chest pain, possible heart attack | 9 | ECG, blood tests, oxygen, nitroglycerin, immediate cardiology consultation |
| 5       | Olivia | 30  | Third-degree burn on hand from kitchen accident | 7 | IV pain relief, burn dressing, possible skin graft consultation |
| 6       | Dante  | 15  | Sprained ankle from basketball game | 5 | X-ray, compression wrap, ice, crutches |
MARKDOWN
